GDB Command Cheatsheet:
gdb <program>
• starts the executable with specific program
run
• runs the program
quit
• Exits the gdb program
help
• Displays information about GDB classes of commands
help all
• Displays all of the commands
break main
• set a breakpoint on the main function
disable 1
• turns off the breakpoint at the first function
delete
• deletes all breakpoints
step or si
• steps into the program or single step
next or ni
• steps over a function
info all-registers
• print all registers
x/xw $esp
• examines one word of memory at the address of the esp and it will display at
hexidecimal
